Text.SourceString: Do you think they might ever open a different bakery on this island?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think they might ever open a different bakery on this island?

Text.SourceString: Oh! I meant in this town… ‘Cause that would be amazing. I would love to meet more bakers.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I meant in this town… ‘Cause that would be amazing. I would love to meet more bakers.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad for stray animals. I wish we can build them houses inside the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad for stray animals. I wish we can build them houses inside the forest.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I suppose there are plenty of trees and caves for them to shelter. But I just want to be sure, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I suppose there are plenty of trees and caves for them to shelter. But I just want to be sure, you know.

Text.SourceString: Can you imagine building a big mansion where the recycling center is?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you imagine building a big mansion where the recycling center is?

Text.SourceString: That would be breathtaking. With the view! Right in front of the vineyard and next to a community center.
Text.LocalizedString: That would be breathtaking. With the view! Right in front of the vineyard and next to a community center.

Text.SourceString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me? Oh no! Today is my day off.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me? Oh no! Today is my day off.

Text.SourceString: You found me! Yeah, I like to spend my day off around the park and hiking somewhere pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: You found me! Yeah, I like to spend my day off around the park and hiking somewhere pretty.

Text.SourceString: I don’t even know where to begin. I have lots of dreams. For instance, I would love to open my own bakery someday once I master pies and cakes.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t even know where to begin. I have lots of dreams. For instance, I would love to open my own bakery someday once I master pies and cakes.

Text.SourceString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.

Text.SourceString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks but that’s no perfume. I think the scent that you smelled was from the cookies that I baked. I bake cookies like all the time at Sam's. They are always sold-out.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks but that’s no perfume. I think the scent that you smelled was from the cookies that I baked. I bake cookies like all the time at Sam's. They are always sold-out.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I don’t mind at all! I love baking. Besides, I get to keep some of them for myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I don’t mind at all! I love baking. Besides, I get to keep some of them for myself.

Text.SourceString: How are you doing today?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you doing today?

Text.SourceString: Yes, I work regular hours today. No big deal though, I like baking.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, I work regular hours today. No big deal though, I like baking.

Text.SourceString: Also, I get to come out of the kitchen, smelling like cookies. Who doesn’t love that?!
Text.LocalizedString: Also, I get to come out of the kitchen, smelling like cookies. Who doesn’t love that?!

Text.SourceString: Hello, neighbor! Another Wednesday, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: Hello, neighbor! Another Wednesday, eh?

Text.SourceString: The food here is so yum. Lodeh, popiah, fried rice... I have to teach myself to make them one of these days.
Text.LocalizedString: The food here is so yum. Lodeh, popiah, fried rice... I have to teach myself to make them one of these days.

Text.SourceString: *sigh*
Text.LocalizedString: *sigh*

Text.SourceString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me? Oh no. Wednesday is my day off.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me? Oh no. Wednesday is my day off.

Text.SourceString: Umm… No baking for me today. I would rather spend my day off around the park or knit something pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… No baking for me today. I would rather spend my day off around the park or knit something pretty.

Text.SourceString: I love the lake in the winter when everything is rigid and frozen... It looks so clean and pretty. Mesmerizing to look at.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the lake in the winter when everything is rigid and frozen... It looks so clean and pretty. Mesmerizing to look at.

Text.SourceString: Sunday is special for me. I hang out at the tavern with Betty after work. Girls night in... Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.
Text.LocalizedString: Sunday is special for me. I hang out at the tavern with Betty after work. Girls night in... Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.

Text.SourceString: I love how Betty and I can just talk and talk about baking... And red velvet. Yum! It turns out that we have a lot in common.
Text.LocalizedString: I love how Betty and I can just talk and talk about baking... And red velvet. Yum! It turns out that we have a lot in common.

Text.SourceString: You found me! What's up?
Text.LocalizedString: You found me! What's up?

Text.SourceString: I opened my window this morning, and the mist woke me up instantly.
Text.LocalizedString: I opened my window this morning, and the mist woke me up instantly.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I just love your style! I like to pay attention to people's outfits around here. You know, for inspiration.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I just love your style! I like to pay attention to people's outfits around here. You know, for inspiration.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith. You moved to an island and changed a career path.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith. You moved to an island and changed a career path.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I can ever do that… Not couragous enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I can ever do that… Not couragous enough.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that. I hope I didn't bum you out.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that. I hope I didn't bum you out.

Text.SourceString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.

Text.SourceString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.

Text.SourceString: Ah, you too, huh? The food here makes me miss my parents too.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, you too, huh? The food here makes me miss my parents too.

Text.SourceString: *sigh*
Text.LocalizedString: *sigh*

Text.SourceString: It really was. So yum! I don't know what I would do if Frank stopped making red velvet cakes.
Text.LocalizedString: It really was. So yum! I don't know what I would do if Frank stopped making red velvet cakes.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I did. I tried copying Frank’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine isn't as good...
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I did. I tried copying Frank’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine isn't as good...

Text.SourceString: For some reason, I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays. You know, maybe it's a celebratory thing. Maybe... In my mind, red velvet cakes equate to the end of a week. I don't know.
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays. You know, maybe it's a celebratory thing. Maybe... In my mind, red velvet cakes equate to the end of a week. I don't know.

Text.SourceString: Hmm... Do you think there is like a green velvet cake? Should I try making it with lettuce? Doesn’t sound very appealing to be honest.

Text.SourceString: There is nothing else that I can do around here anyway. So I might as well bake. Besides, baking is fun.

Text.SourceString: That’s Macy. She’s the one who has a cool pet lobster... Well, it's not much of a pet, really. More like a rescue. Pretty eccentric gal, she is...
Text.LocalizedString: That’s Macy. She’s the one who has a cool pet lobster... Well, it's not much of a pet, really. More like a rescue. Pretty eccentric gal, she is...

Text.SourceString: You’re right. Macy loves pizza and wine. She said that they remind her of home... I think she's pretty close with her folks. She talks about them a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re right. Macy loves pizza and wine. She said that they remind her of home... I think she's pretty close with her folks. She talks about them a lot.

Text.SourceString: You must be busy on Mondays, huh? Running such a big farm like yours must take a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: You must be busy on Mondays, huh? Running such a big farm like yours must take a lot.

Text.SourceString: Not just energy. It takes a lot of patience and dedication, I'm sure.
Text.LocalizedString: Not just energy. It takes a lot of patience and dedication, I'm sure.

Text.SourceString: What are you up to, Player?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you up to, Player?

Text.SourceString: I sew after work... Ah, for fun. The inn has a community sewing machine in the lobby, so why not.
Text.LocalizedString: I sew after work... Ah, for fun. The inn has a community sewing machine in the lobby, so why not.

Text.SourceString: Many things… But I mostly sew decorative pillows. They're gorgeous and easy to make.
Text.LocalizedString: Many things… But I mostly sew decorative pillows. They're gorgeous and easy to make.

Text.SourceString: Decorative pillows are so expensive. That's why I am making my own.
Text.LocalizedString: Decorative pillows are so expensive. That's why I am making my own.

Text.SourceString: So true, decorative pillows are impractical. But they look so dashing on furniture! Can't help myself.
Text.LocalizedString: So true, decorative pillows are impractical. But they look so dashing on furniture! Can't help myself.

Text.SourceString: Just work... Watch some tv, then rest. Sounds so dull when I say it out loud.
Text.LocalizedString: Just work... Watch some tv, then rest. Sounds so dull when I say it out loud.

Text.SourceString: Can your farm make truffle oil? The mayor loves it, by the way. He said that it’s the secret garnish to Carol's stew.
Text.LocalizedString: Can your farm make truffle oil? The mayor loves it, by the way. He said that it’s the secret garnish to Carol's stew.

Text.SourceString: Umm… Haven’t you heard? Carol is Mayor Connor's late wife. May she rest in peace...
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… Haven’t you heard? Carol is Mayor Connor's late wife. May she rest in peace...

Text.SourceString: I had a slice of bread for a quick breakfast this morning... That and some fruits from the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a slice of bread for a quick breakfast this morning... That and some fruits from the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: There are still things that I want to see in this world. Like, I'm sure that there is more to life than baking cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: There are still things that I want to see in this world. Like, I'm sure that there is more to life than baking cookies.

Text.SourceString: Maybe farming... Or swimming with dolphins. Go hiking up the mountain and see the stars up close. I haven't done those stuff just yet.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe farming... Or swimming with dolphins. Go hiking up the mountain and see the stars up close. I haven't done those stuff just yet.

Text.SourceString: I work from 12-5 on Sundays. What about you?
Text.LocalizedString: I work from 12-5 on Sundays. What about you?

Text.SourceString: Are you done for the day? I don’t know how much workload farmers have.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you done for the day? I don’t know how much workload farmers have.

Text.SourceString: Do you like to visit the museum? I see you go in and out of there pretty often.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like to visit the museum? I see you go in and out of there pretty often.

Text.SourceString: Oh, gotcha. Me neither... It’s too quiet for my taste. It'd put me right to sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, gotcha. Me neither... It’s too quiet for my taste. It'd put me right to sleep.
